00:16:43.239 --> 00:16:47.159
So serial organizers seem to be integral into getting things up

00:16:47.159 --> 00:16:48.280
and running.

00:16:48.280 --> 00:16:50.719
But that adds strain on just a few people.

00:16:50.719 --> 00:16:53.520
So do you think that's sort of always how it's going to be?

00:16:53.520 --> 00:16:56.440
Or can you imagine that as something that will change?

00:16:56.440 --> 00:17:00.640
So I guess, you know, and I think

00:17:00.640 --> 00:17:03.039
the best test of an organization is

00:17:03.039 --> 00:17:07.160
whether you're able to leave it and it keeps on thriving.

00:17:07.160 --> 00:17:09.760
But it takes a lot of effort to get there.

00:17:09.760 --> 00:17:13.119
And it takes a lot of dedication for the core group.

00:17:13.119 --> 00:17:19.599
So I think a lot of the times, and I

00:17:19.599 --> 00:17:21.680
think the Our Ladies Organization Guide has

00:17:21.680 --> 00:17:23.800
a lot of thoughts on this, is like being

00:17:23.800 --> 00:17:26.800
able to kind of split things into roles

00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:31.599
and basically make sure that no one person is

00:17:31.599 --> 00:17:33.920
doing all of the work.

00:17:33.920 --> 00:17:36.920
And so yeah, basically take all of Reva's advice

00:17:36.920 --> 00:17:39.880
and make it modular.

00:17:39.880 --> 00:17:40.760
All right, fantastic.

